[normal]&#xa0;[bold]1.
[normal] [bold]About diabetes
[normal] [bold]&#xa0;[bold]1.1
[normal] [bold]Type 1
[normal] [bold]diabetes develops if the body ca
[normal]nnot produce any insulin. 
[normal]About 10%
[normal] of people with diabetes have Type 1.
[normal] It cannot be prevented
[normal] and 
[normal]is treated by daily insulin doses by injections or via an insulin pump
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.2
[normal] [bold]Type 2
[normal] [bold]diabetes develops when the body can still make some insulin, but not enough, or when the insulin that is produced does not work properly
[normal] (known as insulin resistance). 
[normal]It
[normal] usually appears in p
[normal]eople over 40
[normal] and 
[normal]accounts for around 
[normal]90
[normal]%
[normal] of people
[normal] with diabetes. I
[normal]t
[normal] is treated with a healthy diet and increased physical activity. 
[normal]T
[normal]ablets and/or insulin can be required.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.3
[normal] 
[normal]Diabetes is
[normal] one of the biggest health 
[normal]challenges of our time: 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Cost of diabetes:[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
